line=6 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=144.01,475.0,541.06,487.0             :              Verbs and adjectives are usually taken to be two fundamentally different lexical
line=7 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=108.01,463.0,540.21,475.0 :       categories. However, both categories can be predicated of a subject in much the same
line=8 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.06 bbox=108.01,451.0,540.73,463.0 :       way  and may  even be used to describe the same eventualities. Thus, (1a) and (1b) in
line=9 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.38 bbox=108.01,439.0,539.22,451.0 :       English have similar structures and mean almost exactly the same thing, even though one
line=10 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=108.01,427.0,344.29,439.0:       contains an adjective and the other a stative verb.

