doc_id=21 page=2 block_id=2-2 bbox=72.0,607.0,505.48,715.0 label=bt 34 42
line=34 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=72.0,703.0,504.23,715.0                    :Indeed, the Edo  pair is particularly interesting, because the stative verb and adjective
line=35 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,691.0,504.66,703.0        :stand in a systematic derivational relationship to each other. They share the same root
line=36 fonts=F0-12.0,F2-12.0 iscore=0.27 bbox=72.0,679.0,504.58,691.0:mose;  the difference is that the verbal form has no inherent tones, the Low-High tone
line=37 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,667.0,505.15,679.0        :pattern indicating present tense, whereas, the adjectival form has  a fixed level tone
line=38 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,655.0,505.38,667.0        :pattern—Low-Low    in this case. In Edo as in English the adjective differs from the verb
line=39 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,643.0,503.51,655.0        :in the fine points of syntactic distribution; nevertheless, the two can be used in parallel
line=40 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,631.0,505.48,643.0        :ways  to describe essentially the same state. Thus, it is a challenge for the correct theory
line=41 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,619.0,503.48,631.0        :of syntactic categories to do justice to both the similarities between adjectives and verbs
line=42 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,607.0,173.63,619.0        :and their differences.

doc_id=21 page=2 block_id=2-3 bbox=72.0,571.0,504.11,595.0 label=bbt 43 44
line=43 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,583.0,504.11,595.0          :       In fact, most contemporary   theories are more  concerned  with capturing the
line=44 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.09 bbox=72.0,571.0,239.3,583.0:similarities (see (3) for an outline).

doc_id=21 page=2 block_id=2-4 bbox=72.0,499.0,481.3,559.0 label=bbbt 45 49
line=45 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=72.0,547.0,359.93,559.0             :(3)    a. Generative syntax: A is [+N, +V]; V is [–N, +V]
line=46 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.45 bbox=108.0,535.0,405.28,547.0:       b. Formal  Semantics: A and V are both one place predicates.
line=47 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.36 bbox=108.0,523.0,439.64,535.0:       c. Structuralist tradition: A and V differ in inflectional morphology.
line=48 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.23 bbox=108.0,511.0,456.26,523.0:       d. Functionalist approaches: As refer to a simple property; Vs refer to a
line=49 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.23 bbox=126.0,499.0,481.3,511.0 :          dynamic  event. The primary function of As is to modify Ns. (Bhat 1994)

doc_id=21 page=2 block_id=2-5 bbox=72.0,343.0,505.51,487.0 label=bbbbt 50 61
line=50 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=72.0,475.0,505.03,487.0            :In particular, X-bar theory clearly has this intention, as does the formal semantic practice
line=51 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.36 bbox=72.0,463.0,505.51,475.0:of treating both intransitive verbs and adjectives as one-place predicates, denoting sets.
line=52 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,451.0,504.8,463.0 :Nevertheless, in this paper, we  argue that there are important syntactic differences
line=53 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.08 bbox=72.0,439.0,503.4,451.0 :between  verbs and  adjectives that go beyond X-bar  theory, and that these syntactic
line=54 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.38 bbox=72.0,427.0,504.32,439.0:differences are grounded in a basic semantic difference. The key  syntactic difference
line=55 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,415.0,503.6,427.0 :centers around  unaccusativity  phenomena:   adjectives  typically act as unergative
line=56 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.27 bbox=72.0,403.0,505.37,415.0:predicates, whereas comparable  verbs act like unaccusative predicates. We propose to
line=57 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.08 bbox=72.0,391.0,504.24,403.0:explain this fact by attributing very different argument structures to adjectives and stative
line=58 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.33 bbox=72.0,379.0,504.8,391.0 :verbs, drawing on Chierchia’s (1985) theory of properties. Then in the second part of the
line=59 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.33 bbox=72.0,367.0,504.06,379.0:paper we  present three syntactic differences between stative verbs and adjectives in the
line=60 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,355.0,504.3,367.0 :Edo language, which confirm  our basic hypothesis. One of these differences shows up in
line=61 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,343.0,373.61,355.0:English too, while the others are hidden for accidental reasons.

