line=134 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=72.0,559.0,505.3,571.0             :Thus, we  see that whether a given predicate is a verb or an adjective is not simply a
line=135 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.22 bbox=72.0,547.0,504.4,559.0 :trivial matter of inflectional morphology,   but instead  has rather deep  syntactic
line=136 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,535.0,505.16,547.0:consequences.  Indeed, we conjecture that this difference in unaccusativity is a clue to the
line=137 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,523.0,449.6,535.0 :fundamental question of what it means to be an adjective as opposed to a verb.

