line=139 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,475.0,503.27,487.0           :       How  can one give a theory of these facts that is consistent with basic assumptions
line=140 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,463.0,503.24,475.0:about how  theta roles are assigned to syntactic positions? Descriptively speaking, the
line=141 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,451.0,505.42,463.0:theme  argument of a verb is an internal argument, whereas the theme argument  of an
line=142 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,439.0,504.07,451.0:adjective is an external argument. However, the very notion of “external argument” is a
line=143 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.21 bbox=72.0,427.0,504.1,439.0 :suspicious one in current theory. Since the advent of the VP-internal subject hypothesis,
line=144 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,415.0,505.33,427.0:it is standard to analyze many external arguments as internal arguments that have been
line=145 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,403.0,503.95,415.0:raised by NP-movement.   Another class of so-called external arguments can be analyzed
line=146 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,391.0,505.09,403.0:as not being arguments of the head at all. Marantz (1984) and Kratzer (1996) take this
line=147 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,379.0,503.02,391.0:view of agent NPs: the reason agents are found outside the VP is that they are not, strictly
line=148 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,367.0,504.07,379.0:speaking, arguments of the verb. Rather (in Kratzer’s version) they are attached to the
line=149 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,355.0,257.95,367.0:clause by a higher functional category.

doc_id=21 page=4 block_id=4-9 bbox=72.0,271.0,505.22,343.0 label=bbbbbbbt 150 155
line=150 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,331.0,504.66,343.0           :       Our basic thesis is that the same thing is true of theme arguments with respect to
line=151 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,319.0,503.92,331.0:adjectives. The  theme  is not, strictly speaking, the external argument of an adjective;
line=152 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,307.0,505.22,319.0:rather it is not an argument of the adjective at all. Therefore if it appears anywhere it
line=153 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,295.0,504.25,307.0:must  be outside the maximal projection of the adjective. In contrast, the theme is an
line=154 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,283.0,503.42,295.0:argument  of the verb; hence it must be an internal argument, because all arguments are.
line=155 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.27 bbox=72.0,271.0,329.29,283.0:Thus, simple argument structures are as shown in (9).

