doc_id=21 page=8 block_id=8-5 bbox=72.0,463.0,505.28,571.0 label=bbbbt 301 309
line=301 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,559.0,504.93,571.0           :       This contrast follows immediately from our proposal, on the assumption that there
line=302 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.07 bbox=72.0,547.0,504.92,559.0:is no covert functional structure in the small clause complement.   Our claim  is that
line=303 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,535.0,504.3,547.0 :adjectives correspond to properties in their guise of inherently saturated individuals. As
line=304 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,523.0,503.97,535.0:such, they have no theta-role to assign to a specifier position. Therefore, the postverbal
line=305 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,511.0,503.79,523.0:NPs  in (23) are left untheta-marked, and  the sentences are ruled out  by the Theta
line=306 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,499.0,504.87,511.0:Criterion. In contrast, the stative verbs in (22) correspond to propositional functions by
line=307 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.40 bbox=72.0,487.0,503.3,499.0 :hypothesis; hence, they do have a thematic role to assign to the subject. Therefore, while
line=308 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.33 bbox=72.0,475.0,505.28,487.0:the difference  between  verbs  and adjectives  seems  to disappear  in small  clause
line=309 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.17 bbox=72.0,463.0,308.99,475.0:complements  in English, it is accentuated in Edo.

