line=380 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,187.0,540.26,199.0                   :       Recall that verbs have no inherent tones, but the tone pattern indicates the tense: for
line=381 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=108.0,175.0,539.89,187.0       :       example,  Low-High  for the simple present of stative verbs. Adjectives, on the other
line=382 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=108.0,163.0,540.11,175.0       :       hand, do have inherent tones: they are idiosyncratically all High or all Low, depending on
line=383 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=108.0,151.0,538.73,163.0       :       the example. Now   notice that the forms we have called “nominal-2” in the last column
line=384 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.19 bbox=108.0,139.0,541.1,151.0        :       appear to be derived from the adjectival forms by the simple prefixing of a vowel. In
line=385 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.25 bbox=108.0,127.0,539.93,139.0       :       particular, the idiosyncratic tones of the adjectives are maintained in the nominal-2 forms.
line=386 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.07 bbox=108.0,115.0,539.88,127.0       :       In contrast, the nominal-1 forms in the third column show no lexical tone variations: they
line=387 fonts=F0-12.0,F2-12.0 iscore=0.18 bbox=108.0,103.0,540.0,115.0:       uniformly have  high tones on the root, together with a low tone prefix ù- and suffix -
line=388 fonts=F0-12.0,F2-12.0 iscore=0.24 bbox=108.0,91.0,540.58,103.0:       mwèn.   This suggests that the nominal-1 is derived most directly from the underlyingly
line=389 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.15 bbox=108.0,79.0,253.3,91.0          :       toneless verb form of the root.

