line=489 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,487.0,503.4,499.0                    :       What  is special about the past perfective of Edo? The table in (38) gives at least
line=490 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,475.0,505.31,487.0        :part of the answer: the past perfective is the only tense/aspect category in Edo that is
line=491 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,463.0,503.93,475.0        :realized as an inflectional affix with segmental content. In particular, it is a suffix
line=492 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.36 bbox=72.0,451.0,504.41,463.0        :consisting of the approximant /r/ and a low-tone vowel  that harmonizes with  the last
line=493 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,439.0,504.86,451.0        :vowel  of the stem. All the other tense/aspect categories in Edo are indicated either by
line=494 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.33 bbox=72.0,427.0,504.96,439.0        :tonal morphemes,   such as the simple  past and present, or by independent  auxiliary
line=495 fonts=F0-12.0,F2-12.0 iscore=0.08 bbox=72.0,415.0,308.33,427.0:particles, such as the future ghá (Agheyisi 1990).

