doc_id=21 page=13 block_id=13-10 bbox=108.0,296.0,540.65,332.0 label=bbtbbtb 549 551
line=549 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,320.0,540.65,332.0            :       The Edoid languages are halfway between Yoruba  and Igbo geographically and socially;
line=550 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.47 bbox=108.0,308.0,540.64,320.0:       this seems also to be true structurally, with part of the verb paradigm like Igbo and part
line=551 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.18 bbox=108.0,296.0,382.66,308.0:       like Yoruba, with implications for the licensing of SVCs.

doc_id=21 page=13 block_id=13-11 bbox=108.0,188.0,540.84,284.0 label=bbtbbbt 552 559
line=552 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=144.0,272.0,539.94,284.0            :              On a still larger scale, SVCs are also found in Khmer and various other South
line=553 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.07 bbox=108.0,260.0,540.84,272.0:       East Asian languages, which (like Yoruba) lack any overt tense/aspect inflection (Schiller
line=554 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.31 bbox=108.0,248.0,540.77,260.0:       1990).  On the other hand, serial-like V-V compounding  is common  in New  Guinean
line=555 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.23 bbox=108.0,236.0,539.03,248.0:       languages like Yimas  and Alamblak,  which  (like Igbo) have rich systems of verbal
line=556 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.21 bbox=108.0,224.0,538.74,236.0:       inflection (Foley and Olsen 1985). Thus, there seems to be a strong negative correlation
line=557 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.29 bbox=108.0,212.0,538.65,224.0:       between the presence of overt inflectional morphology and the possibility of serial verb-
line=558 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.15 bbox=108.0,200.0,539.45,212.0:       like constructions. However, the type of inflectional morphology has no direct impact on
line=559 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.15 bbox=108.0,188.0,458.97,200.0:       the existence of resultative AP constructions, at least in English and Edo.

doc_id=21 page=13 block_id=13-12 bbox=108.0,104.0,540.58,176.0 label=bbtbbbb 560 565
line=560 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=144.0,164.0,539.08,176.0                    :              Unfortunately, there is still no fully satisfying theoretical account of the paradigm
line=561 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.00 bbox=108.0,152.0,538.83,164.0        :       in (39) within the Principles and Parameters  literature. Two main  ideas have been
line=562 fonts=F0-12.0,F2-12.0 iscore=0.13 bbox=108.0,140.0,539.81,152.0:       explored. Jaeggli and Hyams (1993) observe that both come and talk assign some kind of
line=563 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.40 bbox=108.0,128.0,539.5,140.0         :       agent role to the subject position in (39a-c); they claim that this nonstandard theta-role
line=564 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.21 bbox=108.0,116.0,540.58,128.0        :       assignment  impedes   verb raising, making  it impossible for the  verb to check  its
line=565 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.08 bbox=108.0,104.0,349.98,116.0        :       inflectional morphology, as stated roughly in (43).

doc_id=21 page=13 block_id=13-13 bbox=108.0,67.0,510.63,91.0 label=bbb 566 567
line=566 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,79.0,510.63,91.0            :       (43)   A  head cannot raise to T to check its inflectional morphology if it assigns an
line=567 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.33 bbox=144.0,67.0,506.51,79.0:              adjunct theta-role (takes part in θ-identification) (Jaeggli and Hyams 1993)

doc_id=21 page=14 block_id=14-1 bbox=72.0,729.0,384.32,741.0 label=t 568 568
line=568 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=72.0,729.0,384.32,741.0:14             MARK BAKER AND O.T. STEWART

doc_id=21 page=14 block_id=14-2 bbox=72.0,644.0,503.53,704.0 label=btt 569 573
line=569 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=72.0,692.0,503.47,704.0            :In contrast, Pollock (1991) focuses on the licensing relationship that must hold between
line=570 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,680.0,503.53,692.0:the single tense and the two verbs in these constructions. His leading idea is that the
line=571 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.25 bbox=72.0,668.0,503.35,680.0:event arguments of both verbs must be bound by tense, and this becomes impossible if
line=572 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,656.0,503.39,668.0:the tense ends up affixed to one of them for morphological reasons, because it then fails
line=573 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.38 bbox=72.0,644.0,372.25,656.0:to c-command  the second verb (compare also Déchaine 1993).

doc_id=21 page=14 block_id=14-3 bbox=72.0,607.01,473.59,631.01 label=btbtt 574 575
line=574 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=72.0,619.01,473.59,631.01             :(44)   The event position of a predicate must be c-commanded and governed by T.
line=575 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.40 bbox=108.0,607.01,407.62,619.01:       This fails if T ends up as a suffix on one of two parallel heads.

doc_id=21 page=14 block_id=14-4 bbox=72.0,560.0,504.37,596.0 label=btbtb 576 578
line=576 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=72.0,584.0,503.26,596.0            :Both of these leading ideas have some  attraction, but both end up requiring some
line=577 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.20 bbox=72.0,572.0,504.37,584.0:stipulations that do not have good independent motivation, and we do not know how to
line=578 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,560.0,178.31,572.0:choose between them.

doc_id=21 page=14 block_id=14-5 bbox=72.0,379.01,505.54,547.01 label=btbbt 579 592
line=579 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,535.01,504.44,547.01           :       The good  news  is that for the purposes of this paper, we do not really have to
line=580 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.06 bbox=72.0,523.01,505.34,535.01:choose. Our  main goal is to motivate empirically the basic difference between adjectives
line=581 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,511.01,503.12,523.01:and verbs.  According  to our view, stative verbs have both a theme argument and an
line=582 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.27 bbox=72.0,499.01,504.82,511.01:eventuality argument, whereas adjectives by themselves have neither (see (9)). Now, the
line=583 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,487.01,504.79,499.01:theme argument  of the stative verb must somehow be identified with the theme argument
line=584 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,475.01,502.99,487.01:of the first verb in a sentence like (36b); perhaps this prevents verb raising, as in Jaeggli
line=585 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,463.01,504.31,475.01:and Hyam  1993.  Moreover,  the eventuality argument of the stative verb must be bound
line=586 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.12 bbox=72.0,451.01,504.04,463.01:by the sole tense in (36b); perhaps this binding relationship fails once the tense affixes to
line=587 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.24 bbox=72.0,439.01,504.41,451.01:the first verb, as in Pollock 1991 and Déchaine 1993. Either way, the crucial point is that
line=588 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,427.01,504.22,439.01:corresponding  adjective in (36a) does not have  a theme  role to be shared, nor an
line=589 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.31 bbox=72.0,415.01,503.06,427.01:eventuality role to be bound; hence neither kind of constraint rules out (36a) in Edo, or
line=590 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.19 bbox=72.0,403.01,502.9,415.01 :(34a) in English. Hence, our theory of the adjective/verb distinction figures to play a
line=591 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,391.01,505.54,403.01:central role in the explanation of these facts, whatever the details of how SVCs and
line=592 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.13 bbox=72.0,379.01,259.64,391.01:resultative APs are ultimately licensed.

doc_id=21 page=14 block_id=14-6 bbox=72.0,355.01,165.35,367.01 label=btbbbt 593 593
line=593 fonts=F1-12.0 bbox=72.0,355.01,165.35,367.01:7.     Conclusion

doc_id=21 page=14 block_id=14-7 bbox=72.0,235.01,505.34,343.01 label=btbbbb 594 602
line=594 fonts=F0-12.0 bbox=108.0,331.01,505.22,343.01                 :       In this paper, we have shown that there is a fundamental difference between the
line=595 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.29 bbox=72.0,319.01,504.67,331.01      :argument  structures of adjectives and comparable verbs: verbs take theme (and event)
line=596 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,307.01,505.34,319.01      :arguments, whereas adjectives apart from a Pred head do not. This proposal accounts for
line=597 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.14 bbox=72.0,295.01,504.13,307.01      :the long-standing puzzle of why adjectives behave like unergative predicates, whereas
line=598 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,283.01,504.3,295.01       :almost synonymous   verbs pattern as unaccusatives. The proposal also finds relatively
line=599 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.18 bbox=72.0,271.01,503.92,283.01      :direct support from at least three facts about Edo: adjectives can be seen not to head small
line=600 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.35 bbox=72.0,259.01,503.63,271.01      :clauses, adjectives do not form argument-taking nominalizations, and adjectives do not
line=601 fonts=F0-12.0 iscore=0.15 bbox=72.0,247.01,503.53,259.01      :unite with the verb to inhibit the realization of inflectional morphology in resultative
line=602 fonts=F0-12.0,F0-8.0 iscore=0.31 bbox=72.0,235.01,501.0,247.01:constructions. In all these ways, adjectives differ minimally and predictably from verbs.^{3}

